# 🛒 Multi-Chain Grocery Store Sales Analysis (Excel Dashboard)

## 📌 Project Overview
This project involves a comprehensive analysis of 1,980+ transactions across multiple grocery store chains (MegaMart, GreenGrocer, ValuePlus, etc.). Using Excel, 
I performed data cleaning, handled financial anomalies, and built an interactive dashboard to visualize sales trends and store efficiency.

## 🚀 Key Takeaway
This project demonstrates how Excel can be used as a powerful analytics and visualization tool to deliver actionable business insights without the need for advanced BI software.


---

## 📊 Dataset Description
The dataset contains transaction-level grocery store data with the following fields:

- customer_id – Unique identifier for each customer  
- store_name – Grocery store / branch  
- transaction_date – Date of purchase  
- aisle – Product category  
- product_name – Item purchased  
- quantity – Units purchased  
- unit_price – Price per unit  
- total_amount – Quantity × unit price  
- discount_amount – Discount applied  
- final_amount – Amount paid after discount  
- loyalty_points – Loyalty points earned  

---

## ❓ Business Questions
Key questions explored in this analysis include:

- Which stores generate the highest revenue?
- How do sales trends change over time?
- Which aisles and products contribute most to revenue?
- How effective are discounts in driving sales?
- Do customers with higher loyalty points spend more?
- How does store performance compare across locations?

---

## 🧹 Data Cleaning & Preparation
The following steps were performed in Excel:

- Converted raw data into structured Excel Tables
- Standardized date and currency formats
      transaction_date → Date
      quantity, unit_price, discount_amount → Number
      store_name, aisle → Text

- Identified and handled negative or invalid final amounts
Created a helper column:
      =IF(final_amount<0,"Review","OK")

- Validated total amounts using quantity × unit price
- Removed duplicate records
- Created time-based fields (Year, Month, Year-Month) for trend analysis
        Year	=YEAR(transaction_date)
        Month	=TEXT(transaction_date,"mmm")
        Discount %	=discount_amount / total_amount
        Revenue Flag	=IF(final_amount>0,"Valid","Error")

